Section 1:
1 L.D. 1241
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 INLAND FISHERIES AND WILDLIFE
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 816, L.D. 1241, “An Act to Establish
10 the Make Change for Wildlife Program to Support the Maine Endangered and Nongame
11 Wildlife Fund”
12 Amend the bill by striking out all of sections 2 and 3 and inserting the following:
13 'Sec. 2. 12 MRSA §10253, sub-§6 is enacted to read:
14 6. Make Change for Wildlife program. The Make Change for Wildlife program is
15 established to encourage voluntary support for the fund from businesses that collect
16 voluntary customer contributions at the point of sale. Businesses shall deposit
17 contributions collected under this subsection with the Treasurer of State and designate
18 those contributions for deposit in the fund. The Treasurer of State shall credit all
19 contributions to the fund and all money generated pursuant to this subsection must be used
20 only for the purposes described in subsection 1.
21 Sec. 3. Report. The Department of Inland Fisheries and Wildlife shall submit a report
22 regarding the Make Change for Wildlife program, established in the Maine Revised
23 Statutes, Title 12, section 10253, subsection 6, including any suggested legislation, to the
24 Joint Standing Committee on Inland Fisheries and Wildlife no later than January 1, 2026.
25 The committee may report out a bill based on the report to the Second Regular Session of
26 the 132nd Legislature.'
27 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
28 number to read consecutively.
29 SUMMARY
3300 This amendment removes language from the bill that establishes a corporate income
3311 tax deduction. It also directs the Department of Inland Fisheries and Wildlife to submit a
3322 report to the Joint Standing Committee on Inland Fisheries and Wildlife, no later than
3333 January 1, 2026, regarding the Make Change for Wildlife program established by the bill.
Page 1 - 132LR1991(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 816, L.D. 1241
314 The report may include suggested legislation. The committee is authorized to report out a
325 bill based on the report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.
336 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
347 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR1991(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
